    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-05-24T04:11:07+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-24T04:11:07+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-23T18:41:07Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-23T18:41:07Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A cold front will stall over central SA today as a low pressure system develops near Kangaroo Island. The low is expected to move north over the Eyre Peninsula early in the week, weakening as it moves into NSW. A trough may linger near the southern coasts before weak ridge of high pressure begins to move across SA later in the week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW014" description="North East Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-05-24T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-25T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-23T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-24T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers south of Yunta, medium chance elsewhere. Winds northwest to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending southeast to southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h in the middle of the day. Daytime maximum temperatures between 18 and 22.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:30am to 2:00pm, UV Index predicted to reach 4 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-05-25T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-26T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-24T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-25T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers near the eastern border, slight chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm near the eastern border in the late afternoon and evening. Winds south to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h increasing to 30 km/h before tending west to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h during the day. Overnight temperatures falling to between 8 and 13 with daytime temperatures reaching between 17 and 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-05-26T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-27T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-25T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-26T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers south of Yunta, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm east of Leigh Creek. Winds west to southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching between 17 and 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-05-27T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-28T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-26T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-27T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers about the Gammon Ranges, slight chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm near the eastern border in the afternoon and evening. Winds northwest to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h tending southeast to southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h during the morning then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 10 with daytime temperatures reaching between 17 and 21.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
